article.description: — Brayden Parker's 21 points helped Idaho State defeat Warner Pacific 92-36 on Monday night.
article.headline: Idaho State wins 92-36 against Warner Pacific in season opener
article.linkText: Idaho State wins 92-36 against Warner Pacific in season opener
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- — Brayden Parker's 21 points helped Idaho State defeat Warner Pacific 92-36 on Monday night. Parker also contributed seven rebounds for the Bengals (1-0, Big Sky Conference). Kiree Huie scored 13 points and added 10 rebounds and three blocks. Maleek Arington was 4 of 7 shooting and 3 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points, while adding three steals. Vincent Warren finished with six points for the Knights (0-1). Collin Oestereich added six points for Warner Pacific. In addition, Josiah Castillo finished with six points. NEXT UP Idaho State visits St. Thomas in its next matchup on Friday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
